Backing up a bit more, Cody went at the door again. The door was having none of it, however, and remained stubbornly
shut. Cody regarded it reproachfully. "You're a door," he said. "You're supposed to let people by. That's the whole
point." He wondered vaguely whether there might be something barring the door on the other side, but dismissed the
thought. He couldn't do anything about that from his present location, so the door would simply have to give way to
his more straightforward approach.
